20. How many types of rman retaintion policy ?
👉 2 types
RMAN RETENTION POLICY
         │
         ├── 1. RECOVERY WINDOW
         ├── 2. REDUNDANCY
         └── 3. NONE

👉  RECOVERY WINDOW -- How many days oracle keep old backups. (default 7 - 30 days)
👉  SYNTAX -- CONFIGURE RETENTION POLICY TO RECOVERY WINDOW OF 7 DAYS;

👉 REDUNDANCY -- How many backup copies oracle keep. (standers - 2 copies)
👉 SYNTAX -- CONFIGURE RETENTION POLICY TO REDUNDANCY 2;

🛠️ Commands:

👉 # Recovery Window set karo:
RMAN> CONFIGURE RETENTION POLICY
      TO RECOVERY WINDOW OF 7 DAYS;

👉 # Redundancy set karo:
RMAN> CONFIGURE RETENTION POLICY
      TO REDUNDANCY 2;

👉 # None set karo:
RMAN> CONFIGURE RETENTION POLICY
      TO NONE;

👉 # Current policy check karo:
RMAN> SHOW RETENTION POLICY;

👉 # Obsolete backups dekhna:
RMAN> REPORT OBSOLETE;

👉 # Obsolete backups delete karo:
RMAN> DELETE OBSOLETE;

👉 # Noprompt se delete:
RMAN> DELETE NOPROMPT OBSOLETE;
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------